The Cyprus Problem
- The greek community makes up about 78% of the island, while the Turkish population figure is not known it is the second largest community on the island (25).
- Much of greek cypriot culture is influence by Greece, with much of the popular media originating in Greece (27).
- Seeing the Greek flag flown is common on the island (27).
[ These are examples greek nationalism in Cypriot culture ]
- Turkish Cypriots demand political equality in a solution. Turkish Cypriots want an equal voice to the Greek cypriots (102).



